::Feline::

She stayed in the corner not moving any closer to them.  She wiped 
her face and tried to dry her eyes.  She looked up at them and nodded 
her head. Then looked back down at the floor.   She still kept her 
arms wrapped around herself. She wasn't going to move any closer to 
them and tried to get back further into the corner, but she was 
already against the wall.  


--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "Megan Solmonson" <tmrattrap@h...> wrote:
> 
> 
> 
> * Iron Raptor gave Feline a small pat on the shoulder when she 
thanked her, 
> just trying to calm her to the point that she wouldn't be
sobbing 
any 
> longer. But when she suddenly got up and walked over to the corner 
again 
> Iron Raptor sighed and shook her head, the fembots actions drawing 
more 
> sympathy from her.
> She looked over towards the open door and a smile came across her 
face, glad 
> as ever to see who was standing there.
> Iron Raptor sighed again and shook her head at the shaking fem, 
knowing that 
> she didn't just trust anybot. *
> 
> " Don't worry. He's on our side."
> 
> * She spoke with a smile to prove herself right, gesturing towards 
Prowl 
> with her thumb. But then her optics narrowed and she looked towards 
him 
> without turning her head. *
> 
> " Even if he IS a bit ugly."
> 
> * The smile remained on her lips, and she knew that Prowl would get 
her back 
> for that later. Iron Raptor then looks at Feline with a reassuring 
> expression on her face, letting her know that it was all right to 
sit back 
> down. But then she thought of something that might calm the femm, 
gesturing 
> towards Prowl. *
> 
> " Feline. This is Prowl, our military strategist and field
soldier. 
Prowl. 
> Feline, a new bot to the Maximal forces."
> 
> * She finished with a gesture towards the fembot. Just hoping that 
this 
> would ease the fear that Feline felt, even if just a bit. *
